wrasse
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:in New Zealand often called parrot fish any of various elongated, compressed, usually brilliantly coloured, spiny-finned fishes, including (in warm seas) some important food fishes, as well as some believed poisonous.
