Quote: [Native or Settlers' Name] Wrasse, or Perch .. [Scientific Name] <i>Labrichthys celidota </i> <i>Ibid.</i> 11/384 The Wrasse and Parrotfish are mostly caught outside among the kelp, and with the Spotty are indiscriminately named Kelp-fish by the fishermen, though the term Butterfish is also given to the smaller sorts.
Notes: (P. Thomson, Otago)

